description: Perhaps so called for its musky odour and because it resembles a rat, or perhaps called by an Algonquian name like the Abenaki moskwas, with the spelling altered under the influence of the English words musk and rat.

examples: He also said that minks, muskrats, foxes, coons, and wild mice were found there, but no squirrels.

entries.meaning: Any of several species of shrews in the family Soricidae, especially the Asian house shrew (Suncus murinus).
